00:10:47.980 --> 00:10:50.630
RAHIEL TESFAMARIAM:
We're family, absolutely.

00:10:50.630 --> 00:10:55.870
I've heard you speak a lot about
your evolution and opinions

00:10:55.870 --> 00:10:58.710
about how this film
and your experiences

00:10:58.710 --> 00:11:00.960
kind of relate to a
larger conversation that's

00:11:00.960 --> 00:11:05.000
happening about terrorism
and Islamophobia.

00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:06.770
Can you speak to
some of those things?

00:11:06.770 --> 00:11:07.395
RON DAVIS: Yes.

00:11:10.430 --> 00:11:12.430
When you look at this
film, what we want to show

00:11:12.430 --> 00:11:14.120
is the families.

00:11:14.120 --> 00:11:16.440
Most of the time when you
see the major networks,

00:11:16.440 --> 00:11:20.390
they show the shooter,
and they show the victim.

00:11:20.390 --> 00:11:23.060
As most of the time you cannot
connect with the victim,

00:11:23.060 --> 00:11:27.305
you just start hearing they
had alcohol in their system.

00:11:27.305 --> 00:11:29.190
They had cocaine
in their system.

00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:32.980
They had weed in their
system constantly victimizing

00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:35.440
the victim all over again.

00:11:35.440 --> 00:11:37.330
You never hear
from the families.

00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:39.700
Every once in a while, they'll
pick a few family members

00:11:39.700 --> 00:11:40.950
to come out and say something.

00:11:40.950 --> 00:11:44.630
But, by in large, you don't
get the family members

00:11:44.630 --> 00:11:46.470
to tell the story
of their child,

00:11:46.470 --> 00:11:48.430
to tell the story
of their loved one.

00:11:48.430 --> 00:11:51.760
That's one of the reasons why
we allow the filmmakers to come

00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:53.670
into our home, to
come into our lives

00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:56.540
and make this film, "3 and
1/2 Minutes, 10 Bullets"

00:11:56.540 --> 00:12:01.800
to show when you take a
valuable life-- and all lives

00:12:01.800 --> 00:12:05.980
have value: black,
white, pink, whatever,

00:12:05.980 --> 00:12:09.550
no matter what your religion,
all lives have value.

00:12:09.550 --> 00:12:11.130
They have communities
that love them.

00:12:11.130 --> 00:12:12.504
They have friends
that love them.

00:12:12.504 --> 00:12:14.320
And they have family
that love them.

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:16.490
And we want to show
that in this film.

00:12:16.490 --> 00:12:20.130
Most of the families out
here, they do not get justice.

00:12:20.130 --> 00:12:24.170
We were one of the few families
that got complete justice.

00:12:24.170 --> 00:12:26.710
When I say complete
justice, what I'm saying

00:12:26.710 --> 00:12:31.320
is first degree murder,
life imprisonment,

00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:34.250
no chance of parole.

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:37.000
I'm talking-- you're
not hearing me.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.930
I'm talking first degree
murder, life imprisonment,

00:12:39.930 --> 00:12:41.380
no chance of parole.

00:12:41.380 --> 00:12:44.380
Most of families don't
even get an indictment.

